Cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, cut it into long strips about ½ cm thick. Cut the top off the @red pepper{1} and remove the seeds, cut it into long strips. Drain and thoroughly rinse your @organic lentils{1}.

Heat a #frying pan{} with @olive oil{1%tsp} over a high heat. Fry off the strips of courgette in the pan in batches, remove to one side. Repeat with the red pepper strips.

> You want the veg to char slightly, which is easier with less oil.

Make a vinaigrette with @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @thyme leaves{1%tsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{¼%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}.

> Pull your fingers along the thyme stalk to remove the leaves.

Mix the lentils with the courgette, red pepper, @wild rocket{1} and the vinaigrette. Taste for seasoning and add more salt or pepper as required.

Cut the @halloumi{1} into slices 1 cm thick. Coat in @olive oil{½%tbsp} with the zest from @lemon{½}(zested).

Heat a frying pan over a medium heat. Cook the halloumi for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, until golden brown.

Divide the salad between your #bowls{} and top with the halloumi.